description._content: Digital ID: 482030. Modern styling of the new Cadillac Sixty line is evident in this view of the coupe. Notes: Horizontal bands of the grille are carried completely around the front of the radiator while the broken planes of the top four form the louvres. A 135-horsepower motor assures extremely good performance. The car is being introduced here this week. Source: Photographs of General Motors and Chrysler car and truck models, 1902 - 1938. / 1902-1938. Cadillac - Chrysler - De Soto - Dodge - La Salle - Plymouth. Photographs - Specifications.
